Modifications made in this derivative include (non-exhaustive):

  * Upgrade of the OCR pipeline to PaddleOCR PP-OCRv6 (detection + recognition).
  * Replacement of the orientation/angle model with the
    PP-LCNet_x1_0_textline_ori classifier (input [1,3,80,160], 0/180 degrees).
  * An "embedded models" build mode that compiles the .onnx models and the
    recognition dictionary into C headers, producing a single self-contained
    DLL/LIB with no external model files at runtime.
  * Updated recognition dictionary handling (ppocr_keys_v6.txt, first line
    "blank", no extra '#' / space padding).
  * Improved Windows path handling using UTF-8 / wide-character APIs.
  * Statically linked ONNX Runtime and OpenCV, static CRT (/MT).
  * An extended C ABI (OcrInitEmbedded, OcrDetectMem, per-text-block getters).
  * Pre-built tiny / small / medium Windows x64 variants.

Files that constitute the derivative/modified code include, among others:
  CMakeLists.txt, OcrCRTLinkage.cmake, build.py,
  include/*.h, src/*.cpp,
  模型转二进制/*.py, 测试/*.py

